defs.name: geometry
defs.docs: Defines various geometric structs and functions used to represent objects in 3-dimensional space.

defs.name: vectors
defs.docs: Provides implementations for both 2D and 3D vectors.

defs.name: Vector2
defs.docs:
Represents a vector in 2 dimensional space.
 The fields of this struct are ``f64``, which is unlike `pbrt`'s approach. They have a runtime flag that lets
 the user choose between `f64` and `f32`, which tends to complicate things unnecessarily for a toy renderer
 like this one.
 I have chosen to exclude the indexing operator included in `pbrt`. It doesn't seem important.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: makes a `Vector2`. Equivalent to just building it manually, but in more Java-y style.

defs.name: has_nan
defs.docs: Determines whether any of the fields of this struct are `NaN`.

defs.name: Vector3
defs.docs:
Represents a vector in 3 dimensional space. See notes on `Vector2` for more information about the
 specific implementation.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (x: f64, y: f64, z: f64) -> Vector3
defs.docs: makes a `Vector3`. Equivalent to just building it manually, but in more Java-y style.

defs.name: has_nan
defs.docs: Determines whether any of the fields of this struct are `NaN`.
